0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 204 "5.  Three-dimension
al plots.  Maple can also provide representations for graphs of functi
ons of two variables.  The graphs of such functions are surfaces in th
ree-dimensional space.  The Maple command is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }{TEXT 270 0 "" }
{TEXT 271 4 "plot" }{TEXT 272 2 "3d" }{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 273 4 "ex
pr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 274 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 8 "=range, " }{TEXT 
275 0 "" }{TEXT 276 2 "y=" }{TEXT -1 19 "range [, options]);" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 
277 4 "expr" }{TEXT 281 1 " " }{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic expression" 
}{TEXT 279 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which represents the function to be plo
tted and " }{TEXT 278 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 282 0 "" }
{TEXT 283 1 "y" }{TEXT 284 0 "" }{TEXT -1 44 " are the two independent
 variables used in  " }{TEXT 280 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define th
e function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 4 "The " }{TEXT 285 0 "" }{TEXT 286 6 "plot3d" }{TEXT 287 0 "" }
{TEXT -1 238 " command will generate a surface plot for the function o
ver the rectangular range specfied in the command statement.  The surf
ace plot can be rotated, tipped over and turned around to see the surf
ace plot from all side and all viewpoints." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 278 "For each of the following func
tions provide a plot which shows the graph.  Choose reasonable values \+
for the ranges of x and y.  Rotate, where appropriate, to present a go
od view of the graph.  The last two graphs are implicitly defined func
tions which require the Maple command " }{TEXT 297 0 "" }{TEXT 298 15 
"implicitplot3d " }{TEXT 299 0 "" }{TEXT -1 29 "which is part of the p
ackage " }{TEXT 300 0 "" }{TEXT 301 5 "plots" }{TEXT 302 0 "" }{TEXT 
-1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 
"a.   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "z" "6#%\"zG" }{TEXT -1 5 " =   " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "cos(2*x-y^2)" "6#-%$cosG6#,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*$%\"yGF(!\"\"" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 62 "implicitplot3d(z =cos(2*x-y^2),x=-10..10,y=-10..10,z=-10..10);" 
}}{PARA 13 "" 1 "" {GLPLOT3D 494 272 272 {PLOTDATA 3 "6$-%+ISOSURFACEG
